---
url: /agents/development/architecture.toon
description: >-
  Package architecture map, install data flow, and key design decisions.
---

package_map[12]{name,path,role}:
  binlink,pkg/binlink/,.bin symlink management
  buildmgr,pkg/buildmgr/,Native package detection and rebuild
  cache,pkg/cache/,JSON metadata cache for package resolutions
  config,pkg/config/,TOML configuration loader
  extractor,pkg/extractor/,Parallel tarball download and extraction
  graph,pkg/graph/,Dependency DAG, topological sort, cycle detection
  intel,pkg/intel/,Project intelligence and analysis
  lockfile,pkg/lockfile/,package-lock.json v2/v3 parser
  platform,pkg/platform/,OS/arch detection and worker tuning
  preflight,pkg/preflight/,Pre-install validation
  ui,pkg/ui/,ANSI terminal output and progress bars

install_data_flow:
  - stage: Preflight
    package: preflight
    function: preflight.Run(dir)
    input: project directory
    output: "*Result — validates package.json, lockfile, node/npm in PATH, permissions"
  - stage: Lockfile Parse
    package: lockfile
    function: lockfile.Parse(path)
    input: package-lock.json path
    output: "*LockfileV2 — packages map with version, resolved URL, integrity, dependencies"
  - stage: Graph Build
    package: graph
    functions[2]:
      - graph.NewDependencyGraph().AddNode(name, version, resolved, integrity, deps)
      - graph.TopologicalSort()
    output: "Levels [][]*PackageNode — Kahn-sorted with cycle detection"
  - stage: Extraction
    package: extractor
    function: extractor.ExtractLevel(ctx, jobs)
    input: "[]PackageJob per topological level"
    output: "[]ExtractResult — parallel HTTP GET + SHA512 + gzip/tar + integrity check"
  - stage: Rebuild
    package: buildmgr
    functions[2]:
      - buildmgr.RebuildAll(ctx) — parallel native rebuild
      - buildmgr.RebuildSequential(ctx) — sequential native rebuild
    strategies[4]:
      - prebuild-install (npx, prebuilt binary)
      - node-gyp rebuild (system node-gyp)
      - npm rebuild --foreground-scripts
      - npm rebuild --build-from-source
  - stage: Binlink
    package: binlink
    function: binlink.LinkAllPackages(ctx, pkgPaths)
    output: Creates .bin symlinks (or .cmd wrappers on Windows)

design_decisions:
  zero_external_dependencies: >
    The entire project uses only Go standard library. The TOML parser
    is hand-rolled (pkg/config/toml.go). CLI dispatching uses flag.FlagSet
    with custom buildRouter()/dispatch(). No cobra, urfave/cli, or
    BurntSushi/toml.
  kahn_topological_sort: >
    Dependency graph uses Kahn's algorithm for topological sort. Packages
    are grouped into levels where same-level packages have no interdependencies
    and can be extracted concurrently. Cycles are detected via in-degree
    counting: if fewer nodes visited than total, ErrCycleDetected is returned.
  level_based_extraction: >
    Each topological level is extracted by a goroutine pool. Workers:
    HTTP GET tarball URL -> stream through SHA512 hasher via io.TeeReader
    -> decompress gzip -> extract tar entries. Paths are validated against
    Zip Slip via isPathSafe(). Integrity verified after extraction.
  retry_with_exponential_backoff: >
    Failed downloads retry up to MaxRetries. Backoff = attempt^2 seconds.
    Only network-related errors are retried (timeout, connection, reset,
    refused, EOF, TLS, HTTP 5xx). Integrity mismatch errors are NOT retried.
  npm_fallback: >
    When all extraction attempts fail for a package, the fallbackInstall()
    method runs npm install <pkg>@<version> with --no-audit --ignore-scripts
    --no-package-lock --no-save.
  platform_detection: >
    DetectOS() checks runtime.GOOS and probes /system/build.prop for Android.
    OptimalWorkerCount() factors CPU count and approx RAM for ARM. On Windows,
    symlinks are disabled unless MANPM_FORCE_SYMLINKS is set.
  heavyweight_package_handling: >
    IsHeavyweightBinaryPkg() matches known large packages (canvas, sharp,
    cypress, puppeteer, playwright, esbuild, swc, etc).
    EnvForHeavyweightPkg() returns env vars to skip binary downloads
    (e.g., CYPRESS_INSTALL_BINARY=0, PUPPETEER_SKIP_DOWNLOAD=true).
  dispatch_routing: >
    Commands are dispatched by name match. Alias resolution via aliases map.
    Typo suggestions via levenshtein distance (threshold <= 2) and prefix
    matching. Subcommands use dispatchSub() recursive dispatch.
